node.title: Victoria records 1,007 local COVID-19 cases and three deaths
node.alt: A healthcare worker in PPE looks at a screen while conducting COVID tests.
node.description: There are now 11,501 active cases in Victoria, as the state tightens its quarantine rules in response to the spread of the Omicron variant.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,007 new locally acquired COVID-19 cases and three deaths, as the state tightens its quarantine rules in response to the spread of the Omicron variant.", "There are now 11,501 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 506\u00a0people have died during the state's current Delta outbreak.", "There are 300 COVID-19 patients in Victorian hospitals, with 45 active cases in ICU and 17 patients on ventilators.", "On the weekend, authorities announced all overseas arrivals in Victoria and their household contacts would be required to isolate at home or suitable accommodation for 72 hours, even if they were previously\u00a0eligible for quarantine-free travel.", "The changes, which took effect from 11:59pm Saturday, also mandate 14 days of hotel quarantine for anyone arriving from nine southern African countries where the variant of concern was first identified.", "On Sunday, Chief Health Officer Brett Sutton said while the discovery of the Omicron variant justified the additional measures, it did not put Victoria \"back to square one by any means\".", "More to come.\u00a0", "", "
What COVID-19 travel insurance doesn't cover you for(Emilia Terzon)
"]
